In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation declaring March 25, 2017, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. He highlights the intertwined relationship between Greek and American democracy, with American patriots finding inspiration from the Greeks in their fight for independence. Trump expresses gratitude for Greece's enduring friendship and recognizes their role as an important partner in international engagements and as a strong ally in NATO. He calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.